news.title: Evergrande's $2.6 billion unit stake sale fails as Chinese officials seek to calm nerves
news.para: Once China's top-selling developer and now reeling under more than $300 billion of debt, Evergrande was in talks to sell a 50.1% stake in its Evergrande Property Services arm to smaller rival Hopson Development Holdings.

news.title: Can Fin Homes' net profit dips 4% in Q2 FY22
news.para: Can Fin Homes' net total income stood at Rs 467.88 crore in Q2 FY22, a decline of 11 per cent from Rs 525.81 crore it registered in the corresponding quarter previous year. The board of directors approved the issue of non-convertible debentures, on private placement basis upto an extent of Rs 4,000 crore during the meeting.

news.title: Asian Paints' net profit dips 29% to Rs 605 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Asian Paints' total income stood at Rs 7,234.21 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 33 per cent from Rs 5,432.86 crore it registered in the similar quarter previous year. The board of directors appointed Milind Sarwate as an additional & independent director.

news.title: Nokia renews lease of 5.11 lakh sq ft space at Embassy Manyata in Bengaluru
news.para: The company recently raised Rs 4,600 crore coupon-bearing debt at an interest rate of 6.5%. The proceeds from this debt raise is to be utilized by Embassy REIT to repay its existing zero-coupon bond outstanding of Rs 4,530 crore.

news.title: Panel headed by Kirron Kher to hold first meet to streamline property services
news.para: The SC in its September 7 order, had ordered the administration to set up a committee to streamline the process for the sanction of mutation, grant of occupancy certificate, no-objection certificate and other citizencentric requirements.

news.title: Habitat for Humanity invests Rs 30 million in Tvasta Manufacturing Solutions
news.para: Hestia Partners and Capnetic Investments joined Habitat in investing in the construction technology startup.

news.title: Real estate the major driver of Telangana's gross value added growth since 2014
news.para: Real estate, dwellings and professional services were the main drivers of the services sector, accounting for nearly 35 per cent of its GVA in 2020-21 — the state GVA’s single-largest sub-sector.

news.title: SC dismisses Sebi's appeal against SAT order: PNB Housing Finance
news.para: ​Last week, PNB Housing Finance said that its board of directors have taken the decision to "not proceed with the preferential issue and terminate the share subscription agreements" with the proposed allottees.

news.title: Have no fear, raze illegal constructions: Maharashtra CM to BMC
news.para: Thackeray held a meeting with BMC officials on Wednesday where he directed the administration to take up the issue on a war footing.

news.title: Rs 3 crore fine levied on agencies in NCR over construction & demolition waste
news.para: An amount of approximately Rs 3 crore has been levied as environmental compensation against the defaulting agencies, besides orders issued for stoppage of work at 52 locations.

news.title: Nagpur civic body plans property tax, city survey, stamps registrar works in all zones
news.para: Municipal commissioner Radhakrishnan B and superintendent of land records GB Deberao have planned a pilot project of integration of data and services of NMC’s property tax department and city survey office at Dhantoli Zone.

news.title: Maharashtra government seeks to redevelop slums on Juhu airport
news.para: Chief minister Uddhav Thackeray on Wednesday held a review of slum rehabilitation schemes in the city. The issue of rehabilitating slums on 8,334 acres of central government land in the city was also discussed.

news.title: Shakti Pumps' net profit rises 36% to Rs 20.78 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: The company registered consolidated revenue of Rs 369.77 crore in the quarter ended September 2021, an increase of 83% from Rs 201.74 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Arihant Superstructures' net profit rises 180% year-on-year in Q2 FY22
news.para: Arihant Superstructures has clocked sales bookings of 831 apartments in the first half of the financial year 2021-22 (April-March), registering 159 per cent on-year growth indicating robust sales velocity.

news.title: BMC clears cash payout for its project-hit tenants, even slums
news.para: A senior civic official said as part of the cash compensation scheme, project-affected persons (PAPs) living in structures built before 1964, known as tolerated structures, will be given compensation based on market rates.
